text: Benobble is a locality in the Scenic Rim Region, Queensland, Australia. == History == Benobble railway station () was on the Cangungra railway line, which operated from 1915 to 1955. ==Census Data== Benobble has a population of 43 at the . The locality contains 17 households, in which 51.4% of the population are males and 48.6% of the population are females with a median age of 34, 4 below above the national average. The average weekly household income is $1,416, $22 below the national average. == References == Category:Scenic Rim Region Category:Localities in Queensland
